Honestly, as much as I hate saying this, ... PowerShell (if we count scripting languages). Everybody has Windows. Just open the command prompt and learn some commands. In a perfect world we'd all have Linux; then my answer would have been Bash.

If we exclude scripting, ... C. Portable. Talks to hardware. Does not have specialty inclinations like scripting languages, so it's also versatile. You'll learn about the importance of memory security. 